review.reviewBody:
Julia Child had a recipe for pork chops, thyme, cream and mustard in her first "Mastering the Art..." from what - 40+ years ago. It's a common French-style recipe for pork chops. 
Most of the time, I saute' minced shallots and a minced clove or two of garlic before adding in the heavy cream. Sauce is delicious spooned over oven-roasted potatoes.

@KevinMofM - you can easily use dried thyme if you don't have fresh. Do it all the thyme.

